<br>
And no, I am not deluded into thinking EQ is all RP, but yes...I do make items and loot take a backseat to my RP experience.<br>
<br>
Friends are hard to loose...that is why I play on MT and FV as of now...but when the world you play in (MT for example) makes the game feel dull and lifeless, well sometimes the move and possible loss is worth it.<br>
<br>
FV is a baby server still...epics, horses, and loot are rare...certain areas of the world that are 'safe' and settled on other worlds are wild and untamed (Desert of Ro is a good example!), and the server is specificaly geared towards roleplaying.  Yes not everyone will agree with the rule set, I happen to love it all and only worry about some of the problems the TLC makes...but overall the server has show me (Still a very young player) that is is filled with roleplayers who are willing to take time to play in character with you and make the adventure mean more.<br>
<br>
Thanks again for all the input, I look forward to more time on the server even more.<br>
